    <h1 class="hero-h">ChatGPT vs Claude<br/><em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">for your business.</em></h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">We implement both. For most small business workflows, writing, research, analysis, client comms, Claude is the better tool. Here's the honest breakdown.</p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a href="#contact" class="btn-p">Get Claude Implemented →</a>
      <a href="/services/implementation" class="btn-g">How We Implement</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<section style="background:#0A1A0A;">
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">Honest comparison</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Feature by feature.</h2>
    <p class="sub">From people who use both tools daily to build real business workflows.</p>
    <div style="overflow-x:auto;">
      <table class="compare-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Feature</th>
            <th>ChatGPT</th>
            <th>Claude</th>
            <th>Winner</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Long-form writing quality</td>
            <td>Good, often generic</td>
            <td>Excellent, more nuanced</td>
            <td><span class="winner-claude">Claude ✓</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Instruction-following</td>
            <td>Tends to drift on complex tasks</td>
            <td>Reliably follows detailed instructions</td>
            <td><span class="winner-claude">Claude ✓</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Business tone & voice</td>
            <td>Needs heavy prompting</td>
            <td>Adapts naturally to your style</td>
            <td><span class="winner-claude">Claude ✓</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Coding & technical tasks</td>
            <td>Strong</td>
            <td>Strong</td>
            <td><span class="winner-tie">Tie</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Image generation</td>
            <td>DALL-E built in</td>
            <td>Not built in</td>
            <td><span class="winner-chatgpt">ChatGPT</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Context window</td>
            <td>128K tokens</td>
            <td>200K tokens</td>
            <td><span class="winner-claude">Claude ✓</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Reasoning & analysis</td>
            <td>Strong with o1/o3</td>
            <td>Excellent natively</td>
            <td><span class="winner-claude">Claude ✓</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Business integrations</td>
            <td>GPT plugins, many options</td>
            <td>Claude.ai + API</td>
            <td><span class="winner-tie">Tie</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Price (Pro tier)</td>
            <td>$20/mo</td>
            <td>$20/mo</td>
            <td><span class="winner-tie">Tie</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Best for SMB workflows</td>
            <td>Decent</td>
            <td>Purpose-built fit</td>
            <td><span class="winner-claude">Claude ✓</span></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">Why Claude wins for SMB</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Six reasons we recommend Claude<br/>for most business teams.</h2>
    <div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-num">01</div>
        <div>
          <div class="step-title">It follows complex instructions reliably</div>
          <div class="step-desc">Multi-step tasks, specific formatting requirements, brand voice rules, Claude follows them consistently. ChatGPT tends to drift on longer or more nuanced prompts.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-num">02</div>
        <div>
          <div class="step-title">Claude Projects is purpose-built for business</div>
          <div class="step-desc">Persistent knowledge base, custom instructions per project, consistent context across sessions. No equivalent in ChatGPT for business workflow use.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-num">03</div>
        <div>
          <div class="step-title">Writing quality is meaningfully better</div>
          <div class="step-desc">For business writing, proposals, client comms, reports, Claude produces cleaner, more natural output with less editing required.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-num">04</div>
        <div>
          <div class="step-title">Larger context window</div>
          <div class="step-desc">Claude handles up to 200K tokens, useful for uploading long documents, RFPs, contracts, or research that ChatGPT would need to truncate.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-num">05</div>
        <div>
          <div class="step-title">Less hedging, more useful output</div>
          <div class="step-desc">Claude is more direct and opinionated in its outputs. You spend less time prompting around refusals to get the business content you actually need.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-row">
        <div class="step-num">06</div>
        <div>
          <div class="step-title">Easier to implement at scale</div>
          <div class="step-desc">The combination of Projects, system prompts, and knowledge bases makes Claude dramatically easier to implement consistently across a team.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="display:flex;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;padding-top:3rem;">
      <a href="/services/implementation" class="btn-g">See Implementation Details →</a>
      <a href="/claude-for-small-business" class="btn-g">Claude for Small Business →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="contact" style="background:#050D05;">
  <div class="sec-inner" style="max-width:680px;">
    <span class="lbl">Get Claude Implemented</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Stop comparing.<br/>Start using Claude properly.</h2>
    <p class="sub">We'll configure Claude for your team and build workflows that prove the decision was right.</p>
    <div id="contact-form">
      <div class="form-grid">
        <div>
          <label class="form-label">First Name</label>
          <input class="input-field" type="text" id="first_name" placeholder="Jane" />
        </div>
        <div>
          <label class="form-label">Last Name</label>
          <input class="input-field" type="text" id="last_name" placeholder="Smith" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="form-field">
        <label class="form-label">Work Email</label>
        <input class="input-field" type="email" id="email" placeholder="jane@company.com" />
      </div>
      <div class="form-field">
        <label class="form-label">Company</label>
        <input class="input-field" type="text" id="company" placeholder="Acme Inc." />
      </div>
      <div class="form-field">
        <label class="form-label">What would you gain if Claude handled the work that's slowing your team down?</label>
        <textarea class="input-field" id="message" placeholder="Faster writing, better research, more capacity..." style="min-height:100px;resize:vertical;"></textarea>
      </div>
      <button class="btn-p" id="submit-btn" style="width:100%;justify-content:center;" onclick="submitForm()">Get Claude Working →</button>
      <p style="font-size:0.75rem;color:#4A6A4A;margin-top:0.75rem;text-align:center;">We respond within one business day. Takes 3 min.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="thankyou" id="thankyou">
      <div class="thankyou-h">You're in good hands.</div>
      <p style="color:#8FAF8F;">We'll be in touch within one business day.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

